    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf we `set cmdheight=0`, we lose the helpful `[2/8]` search count in the very bottom line, and there is a elaborate plugin https://github.com/kevinhwang91/nvim-hlslens does exactly this with 2600 lines of code (it duplicate the search process to get count).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSome way to expose the total match count and current count index via `vim.v`? Expose those values before search ends, during incsearch process will be very helpful too.",
